        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "dx: PR template chooser, justfile, and scripts README index (#59737, #59736, #59728)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThree DX improvements in one PR — all low-risk, non-breaking changes that make contributing to OpenClaw easier.\n\n### #59737 — PR Template Chooser\n\n- Created `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/quick_fix.md` (~30 lines) for small fixes (typos, one-line bugs, minor docs)\n- Copied existing template to `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/full_change.md` for substantial changes\n- Updated `pull_request_template.md` to guide users to the template chooser\n- GitHub shows a template selector on PR creation\n\n### #59736 — Justfile for Common Tasks\n\n- Added `justfile` with 30+ developer tasks\n- `just --list` shows all available tasks with descriptions\n- Covers: build, test, check, lint, format, dev, config, maintenance, plugin SDK\n- Alternative to remembering 398 package.json scripts\n\n### #59728 — Scripts Directory README Index\n\n- Created `scripts/README.md` organizing 318 files into 13 functional categories\n- Each category has a table with script names and descriptions\n- Covers: Check/Validation (61), Test/Benchmark (37), Config/Generation (23), Build (9), CI (7), Plugin (10), Release (5), Docs (10), Platform (10), Security (1), and more\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Docs\n- [x] Chore/infra\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] CI/CD / infra\n- [x] UI / DX\n\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\n\n- PR creation now shows a template chooser (Quick Fix vs Full Change)\n- `just --list` works from repo root\n- `scripts/README.md` is browsable on GitHub\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- No new permissions or capabilities\n- No secrets/tokens handling changed\n- No new/changed network calls\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n- None. All changes are additive (new files) with one non-breaking modification to the existing PR template.\n",
